From: SJ Park <sj@kernel.org>
Date: Sat, 4 Jul 2026 13:35:13 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] mm/damon: remove has_probe_weights

It is easy to make bug, remove it.

Signed-off-by: SJ Park <sj@kernel.org>
---
 include/linux/damon.h | 3 ---
 1 file changed, 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/include/linux/damon.h b/include/linux/damon.h
index bbbba320cbb6f..a7e6ede52cc32 100644
--- a/include/linux/damon.h
+++ b/include/linux/damon.h
@@ -898,9 +898,6 @@ struct damon_ctx {
 	struct list_head schemes;
 
 	struct rnd_state rnd_state;
-
-	/* has non-zero probe weights */
-	bool has_probe_weights;
 };
 
 /* Get a random number in [@l, @r) using @ctx's lockless PRNG. */
-- 
2.47.3

